Text Mode displays the fields which are to be edited.  To change information in
fields, type the new information and it will replace the old information.  To
insert characters in the middle of the field, press the insert key and what is
typed will be inserted.  What is on the screen when a function key or the
return key is pressed is what will be saved. 
When using the percent option for entering data, the total field should be
entered to give the component count. If using the component count, the total
field will be skipped.

To obtain help for any of the following subjects,  press the function key next
to the desired subject.

 
        F2  Edit
 
 


 
        F8  Return to Previous Menu
 
        F10 Exit from Help

Press F8 to return to the last menu screen or F10 to leave the help mode
